Stern gave his opinion one hour after the Chinese Secretary of State He Yafei declared that there was either a lack of "reason" for the leading American climate negotiator, or it was "very irresponsible" for him to say at the beginning of the week that the United States would not help China financially to master global warming.
As a result of the future economic march of the great world powers at stake, there have been break lines both within the industrial nations and between the industrial nations and the emerging economies.
The current struggle is equally related to the rescue of individual economists, as well as to the rescue of the planet, where China and the United States were established because of their respective commitments, while poorer countries claim that the two dozen most influential countries would ignore the scientific need to take bolder measures.
Ricardo Ulate, a delegate from Costa Rica, said that it is not surprising that the great powers are fighting for who should bear the cost of braking the greenhouse gas emissions, since even affected countries have gone over to aggressively take action to bring the countries with very high greenhouse gas tax to account for their actions.
