CNMV approves Paterina’s public tender for exclusion submitted by Mer Investment Company
The National Stock Exchange Commission (CNMV) approved the public procurement for Federico Paternina submitted by the Investment Company Mer last 9 October.
The supervisory authority stated that it approved this invitation to tender after it had been proved that the conditions of the law-enforcement legislation are complied with and can therefore be considered as "sufficient" according to the amendments of the last 2 December.
CNMV has also announced that this offer is aimed at acquiring 550,0008 shares from Federico Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, which in turn is 8.95% of the capital of the company, which consists of 6,142,786 euros in shares admitted to Madrid and Bilbao.
Furthermore, it has been announced that 5,592,778 million shares have been fixed, which cannot be transferred in any way until the closing of the tender and whose price has been determined by Federico Paternina in accordance with the laws in force.
