Every day thousands of vehicles that have been involved in an accident are dragged into workshops where an assessor has to assess the damage caused and the cost of repair.
No accident is the same and the calculation of the costs for the parts and hours can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and hours of work, may take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer science tools, it is a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100 % of the experts use this type of system.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from manufacturers to process it afterwards and to offer them to their customers in the form of a useful program.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all reports are produced using their products.
The other two companies competing on the tool market for assessing and drawing up a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data the manufacturers provide is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
Moreover, the volume of data to be processed is becoming increasingly large, up to the point that even more versions, variants and motorizations have been on the market in the last five years than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car arrives on the market, the company starts work.
